## M19(3/6): safe-whitelist builtins are usable outside unsafe context.
##
## Per GPT-5.5 entry 35 (M19 design): pure compile-time type
## queries and meta operations don't require unsafe. The
## whitelist currently covers:
##
##   @sizeOf / @alignOf       - type size / alignment queries
##   @TypeOf / @typeName      - type introspection
##   @hasDecl / @hasField     - meta queries
##   @len                     - array / slice length
##   @This                    - current containing type (in generics)
##
## All of these are pure, ownership-safe, and don't manipulate
## pointers. Adding a new safe builtin requires explicit audit
## per the runtime-comment-encoded criteria.

sub main()
  arr = [1, 2, 3]
  n = @len(arr)              # OK: @len is safe
  print(n)
